1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. exd5 cxd5 4. Bd3 Nc6 5. c3 Qc7 6. Ne2 Bg4 7. O-O e6 8. Qe1 Be7 
{In anticipation of 9. f3, Black takes the h4 square away from the white queen. 
However, White has another way to harass Black's bishop.} 9. Ng3 $1 h5 {The 
principled way to try and justify Black's previous move.} 10. f3 h4 11. fxg4 hxg3 12. 
h3 $1 {Instead of shattering his structure by taking the pawn right away, White hopes 
to collect it later with greater dividends.} Bd6 {Forced, since Bf4 was threatened.} 
13. Na3 $1 {Development with tempo (threatening Nb5)!} a6 14. Nc2 Nge7 15. Bd2 O-O 
16. Kh1 $16 {Not only does White possess a strong bishop pair, he also has prospects 
of eventually taking the g3 pawn.} *

