1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. exd5 cxd5 4. Bd3 Nc6 5. c3 Nf6 6. Bf4 Bg4 7. Qb3 Qc8 8. Nd2 e6 
9. Ngf3 Be7 10. O-O Bh5 11. Rae1 O-O 12. Qc2 Bg6 13. Bxg6 hxg6 14. Qd3 {This 
innocous-looking move hides a venomous idea.} a6 15. Ng5 $1 Nh5 16. Qh3 $1 {The point 
behind 14.Qd3. The bishop is untouchable and White will continue to amass his forces 
on the kingside - Ndf3, Re3, Re1. A well-timed seizure of the h file by means of g4, 
Qh4 and Rh3 could simply end the game. Black is in serious trouble.} *

