1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. exd5 cxd5 4. Bd3 Nc6 5. c3 Nf6 6. Bf4 Bg4 7. Qb3 Qc8 8. Nd2 e6 
9. Ngf3 Be7 10. O-O O-O {This move, although most often played, is innacurate, as 
Black's bishop will not succeed to get to g6 without being exchanged for the white 
knight.} 11. Ne5 $1 Bh5 12. Qc2 Bg6 {Again the most often played move is hardly the 
best one. Black does not have to give up his light-squared bishop yet - see the 
12....Bd6 line.} 13. Nxg6 hxg6 14. Nf3 $14 {White's pair of bishops gives him a 
long-lasting edge.} *

