9. Ngf3 Be7 10. O-O O-O 11. Ne5 Nxe5 12. dxe5 Nd7 13. Qc2 g6 14. Rfc1 $1 Bf5 15. Bxf5 
gxf5 {15....ef5 is of course possible as well, but then after 16. Nf3 Black's 
weakened structure must offer White a stable advantage in my view. The move in the 
game, on the other hand, requires concrete reaction from White.} 16. Qd1 $1 {A very 
strong move, preparing both c4 and Qh5. White is firmly in control.} *

