1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. exd5 cxd5 4. Bd3 Nc6 5. c3 g6 6. Nf3 Bg7 7. O-O Nh6 8. Re1 O-O 
9. Bf4 f6 10. c4 Bg4 11. cxd5 Nxd4 12. Bc4 Bxf3 {As I said in the main line, this is 
even worse for Black than 12....Nhf5} 13. Qxd4 $1 e5 {The only move.} 14. Qe3 exf4 
15. Qxf3 $16 {The f4 pawn is bound to fall. Black retains some hope of defence by 
establishing a blockade on the d6 square, but of course White should be more than 
happy to emerge out of opening with a position like this.} *

