1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. exd5 cxd5 4. Bd3 Nc6 5. c3 g6 6. Nf3 Bg7 7. O-O Nh6 {By 
developing his knight to h6, Black intends to strike in the centre with ...f6 and 
...e5. White should be quick to anticipate this plan with c4 break.} 8. Re1 O-O 9. 
Bf4 f6 10. c4 $1 {The key move. Now Black is not in time to play ...e5 and his centre 
crumbles.} Bg4 11. cxd5 Nxd4 12. Bc4 Nhf5 {An alternative 12....Bxf3 is even worse.} 
13. d6+ e6 14. Bxe6+ Nxe6 15. Rxe6 Qd7 16. Qd5 Qc6 17. Qxc6 bxc6 18. Nbd2 $16 
{Black's bishop pair offers him some chances of holding this endgame, but White has 
every reason to be optimistic holding an extra passed pawn on the 6th rank.} *

