1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. exd5 cxd5 4. Bd3 Nc6 5. c3 g6 6. Nf3 Bf5 {This is probably the 
most appealing move order for this exchange. Black retains an option to develop his 
dar-squared bishop to d6, which is certainly a better place than g7. Neverthless, I 
have found an antidote to this plan.} 7. Bxf5 gxf5 8. Bg5 $1 {This move disables both 
...e6 and ...Nf6 forcing Black to develop his bishop to g7.} Bg7 9. Nbd2 Nf6 10. O-O 
O-O 11. Ne1 $14 {The play assumes the same character as in the 6....Nf6, 9....Bf5 
line and White is all the same better.} *

